    <!-- FAQ SECTION -->
    <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions About BCAA Gummies</h2>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>What are BCAAs and why do they matter for recovery?</summary>
      <p>BCAAs (leucine, isoleucine, valine) are three essential amino acids that comprise 35% of muscle protein. Leucine activates the mTOR pathway for muscle protein synthesis. BCAAs reduce exercise-induced muscle damage by 22% and DOMS by up to 33%. The 2:1:1 ratio is the most studied and recommended.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Do BCAA gummies work as well as BCAA powder?</summary>
      <p>They deliver the same amino acids but at lower doses (1-3.5g vs 5-10g in powder). Absorption is identical regardless of format. For casual gym-goers, gummy doses are adequate. For competitive athletes, powder may be needed for higher doses. Gummies excel in taste and compliance.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>When should I take BCAA gummies?</summary>
      <p>Best timing: 30 minutes before exercise, during prolonged sessions, or within 30 minutes after. Post-workout is the single most impactful timing. On rest days, take with a meal. Consistency matters more than perfect timing.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Do I need BCAAs if I already take protein?</summary>
      <p>If you consume 0.7-1g protein per pound of body weight daily, you may get sufficient BCAAs from diet. However, BCAAs benefit fasted training, very high training volumes, and caloric deficits. They are most valuable for people who struggle to hit daily protein targets.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>What is the ideal BCAA ratio?</summary>
      <p>The 2:1:1 leucine:isoleucine:valine ratio is the evidence-based standard. It mirrors natural muscle tissue proportions and provides enough leucine to activate mTOR. Higher ratios (4:1:1, 8:1:1) have not been consistently shown to be superior in clinical trials.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Are BCAA gummies safe?</summary>
      <p>BCAAs are extensively studied and safe for healthy adults at 3-10g daily. Side effects are rare. People with maple syrup urine disease (MSUD) must avoid BCAAs. Those with kidney or liver disease should consult their physician first.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>How long does it take for BCAAs to work?</summary>
      <p>Blood levels peak within 30-60 minutes. Reduced soreness is noticeable within a few sessions. Cumulative recovery benefits appear after 1-2 weeks of daily use. Muscle preservation benefits during cutting phases emerge over 4-8 weeks.</p>
    </details>

